        "html_content": "<div style=\" padding: 2.5rem; border: 0.0625rem solid #ccc; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: space-between; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;\"><div style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; align-items: center; height: 100%;\"><h2 style=\"display: none;\">Page 1</h2><p><img style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;\" alt=\"original image\"></p><div style=\"font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.4; color: #555;\"><p style=\"font-weight: bold; margin: 0;\">kieso<br>weygandt<br>warfield</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.9375rem; font-weight: bold; color: #004d99;\">team for success</p></div><h1 style=\"font-size: 3em; margin: 1.875rem 0; color: #004d99; line-height: 1.1;\">INTERMEDIATE<br>ACCOUNTING<br>SECOND EDITION</h1><div style=\"font-size: 0.9em; color: #777; margin-top: 1.875rem;\"><p style=\"margin: 0;\">Prepared by<br>Coby Harmon<br>University of California, Santa Barbara<br>Westmont College</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.25rem; font-weight: bold; color: #004d99; font-size: 1.2em;\">WILEY</p></div></div></div>"
      },
      {
        "id": "ch4-p2",
        "type": "equation",
        "html_content": "<div style=\"overflow: scroll; padding: 2.5rem; border: 0.0625rem solid #ccc; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff; display: flex; flex-direction: column; box-sizing: border-box;\"><div style=\"color: #555; font-size: 0.9em; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 0.3125rem;\">Intermediate Accounting • IFRS 2nd Edition • Kieso, Weygandt, and Warfield</div><h1 style=\"color: #333; border-bottom: 0.1875rem solid #004d99; padding-bottom: 0.625rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;\">PREVIEW OF CHAPTER 4</h1><div style=\"flex-grow: 1; overflow-y: auto;\"><div style=\"border: 0.0625rem dashed #004d99; padding: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; background-color: #f4f8fc; font-size: 0.9em; color: #333;\"><strong style=\"color: #004d99; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.625rem;\">Chapter Structure Flowchart</strong> <p style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0.3125rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.4;\">graph TD\n    A[Income Statement and Related Information] --> B[Income Statement]\n    A --> C[Format of the Income Statement]\n    A --> D[Reporting within the Income Statement]\n    A --> E[Other Reporting Issues]\nsubgraph Income Statement\n    B1[Usefulness]\n    B2[Limitations]\n    B3[Quality of earnings]\nend\n...</p></div><h2 style=\"color: #004d99; margin-top: 0.625rem; margin-bottom: 0.3125rem; font-size: 1.3em;\">Income Statement</h2><ul style=\"list-style-type: square; margin-left: 1.25rem; padding-left: 0; font-size: 0.95em; color: #333;\"><li>Usefulness</li><li>Limitations</li><li>Quality of earnings</li></ul><h2 style=\"color: #004d99; margin-top: 0.625rem; margin-bottom: 0.3125rem; font-size: 1.3em;\">Format of the Income Statement</h2><ul style=\"list-style-type: square; margin-left: 1.25rem; padding-left: 0; font-size: 0.95em; color: #333;\"><li>Elements</li><li>Intermediate components</li><li>Illustration</li><li>Condensed income statements</li></ul><h2 style=\"color: #004d99; margin-top: 0.625rem; margin-bottom: 0.3125rem; font-size: 1.3em;\">Reporting within the Income Statement</h2><ul style=\"list-style-type: square; margin-left: 1.25rem; padding-left: 0; font-size: 0.95em; color: #333;\"><li>Gross profit</li><li>Income from operations</li><li>Income before income tax</li><li>Net income</li><li>Non-controlling interest</li><li>Earnings per share</li><li>Discontinued operations</li><li>Intraperiod tax allocation</li><li>Summary</li></ul><h2 style=\"color: #004d99; margin-top: 0.625rem; margin-bottom: 0.3125rem; font-size: 1.3em;\">Other Reporting Issues</h2><ul style=\"list-style-type: square; margin-left: 1.25rem; padding-left: 0; font-size: 0.95em; color: #333;\"><li>Accounting changes and errors</li><li>Retained earnings statement</li><li>Comprehensive income</li><li>Statement of changes in equity</li></ul></div><div style=\"text-align: right; margin-top: 0.9375rem; font-size: 0.85em; color: #777;\">Slide 4-2</div></div>"
      },
      {
        "id": "ch4-p3",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "html_content": "<div style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; padding: 2.5rem; border: 0.0625rem solid #ccc; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff; display: flex; flex-direction: column; box-sizing: border-box;\"><header style=\"color: #004d99; font-size: 1.8em; font-weight: bold; border-bottom: 0.125rem solid #ccc; padding-bottom: 0.3125rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;\">INCOME STATEMENT</header><h2 style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #333; margin-bottom: 0.625rem; font-size: 1.4em;\">Usefulness</h2><div style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem;\"><div style=\"border-left: 0.25rem solid #004d99; padding-left: 0.9375rem;\"><ul style=\"list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #333; font-size: 1.1em;\"><li>Evaluate past performance.</li></ul><p style=\"font-size: 0.9em; color: #555; margin-top: 0.3125rem; margin-bottom: 0;\">&lt;img style='max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin-top: 0.625rem;' alt='A cartoon businessman pointing at a rising line graph on a screen that shows “GE Profits.” The caption beneath reads, “Hmmm… Where am I headed?”'&gt;</p></div><div style=\"border-left: 0.25rem solid #004d99; padding-left: 0.9375rem;\"><ul style=\"list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #333; font-size: 1.1em;\"><li>Predict future performance.</li></ul><p style=\"font-size: 0.9em; color: #555; margin-top: 0.3125rem; margin-bottom: 0;\">"
      },
      {
        "id": "ch4-p4",
        "type": "equation",
        "html_content": "<div style=\"border: 0.0625rem solid #000; padding: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; background-color: #e6f7ff;\">\n    <h2 style=\"text-align: right; color: #333; border-bottom: 0.125rem solid #333; padding-bottom: 0.3125rem;\">Page 4</h2>\n    \n    <header style=\"font-size: 2.5em; font-weight: bold; color: #004d40; border-bottom: 0.1875rem solid #004d40; text-align: center; padding-bottom: 0.625rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;\">INCOME STATEMENT</header>\n    \n    <p style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color: #004d40;\"><strong>Usefulness</strong></p>\n    \n    <ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.4;\">\n        <li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Evaluate past performance.</span></li>\n    </ul>\n    <div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0.625rem 0; border: 0.0625rem dotted #aaa; padding: 0.3125rem; background-color: white;\">\n        <p style=\"font-style: italic; color: #555;\">&lt;img&gt;A cartoon businessman pointing at a rising line graph on a screen that shows “GE Profits.” The caption beneath reads, “Hmmm… Where am I headed?”&lt;/img&gt;</p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.4;\">\n        <li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Predict future performance.</span></li>\n    </ul>\n    <div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0.625rem 0; border: 0.0625rem dotted #aaa; padding: 0.3125rem; background-color: white;\">\n        <p style=\"font-style: italic; color: #555;\">&lt;img&gt;A comparison chart titled “Hyundai vs Toyota.” It displays two profit-and-loss balloons: Hyundai (yellow) labeled “Revenues – Expenses / Profits” and Toyota (blue) labeled “Revenues – Expenses / Profits.” An arrow between them indicates Toyota’s higher profitability, with the caption, “Which company did better last year?”&lt;/img&gt;</p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.4;\">\n        <li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Help assess the risk or uncertainty of achieving future cash flows.</span></li>\n    </ul>\n    <div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0.625rem 0; border: 0.0625rem dotted #aaa; padding: 0.3125rem; background-color: white;\">\n        <p style=\"font-style: italic; color: #555;\">&lt;img&gt;A table titled “Siemens Income for Year Ended 12/31/15.” It lists revenues, operating income, unusual items, and net income. A vertical dashed line on the right asks, “Recurring?” with responses “Yes,” “No,” and “?” beneath it. Below the table, the caption reads, “Recurring items are more certain in the future.”&lt;/img&gt;</p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <p style=\"text-align: right; font-size: 0.8em; color: #999; margin-top: 0.9375rem;\">&lt;page_number&gt;Slide 4-4&lt;/page_number&gt;</p>\n    <p style=\"text-align: right; font-size: 1em; font-weight: bold; color: red;\">LO 1</p>\n</div>\n<hr style=\"border: none; border-top: 0.3125rem solid #000;\" />"
      },
      {
        "id": "ch4-p5",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "html_content": "<div style=\"border: 0.0625rem solid #000; padding: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; background-color: #fffafa;\">\n    <h2 style=\"text-align: right; color: #333; border-bottom: 0.125rem solid #333; padding-bottom: 0.3125rem;\">Page 5</h2>\n    \n    <header style=\"font-size: 2.5em; font-weight: bold; color: #004d40; border-bottom: 0.1875rem solid #004d40; text-align: center; padding-bottom: 0.625rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;\">INCOME STATEMENT</header>\n    \n    <h2 style=\"color: firebrick; margin-bottom: 0.9375rem; border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid firebrick;\">Limitations</h2>\n    \n    <ul style=\"list-style-type: square; margin-left: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.4;\">\n        <li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Companies omit items that cannot be measured reliably.</span></li>\n    </ul>\n    <div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0.625rem 0; border: 0.0625rem dotted #aaa; padding: 0.3125rem; background-color: white;\">\n        <p style=\"font-style: italic; color: #555;\">&lt;img&gt;A woman pushing a shopping cart labeled “Exp,” “Rev,” and “Profits.” A note beside her reads “You left something out!”&lt;/img&gt;</p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <ul style=\"list-style-type: square; margin-left: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.4;\">\n        <li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Income numbers are affected by the accounting methods employed.</span></li>\n    </ul>\n    <div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0.625rem 0; border: 0.0625rem dotted #aaa; padding: 0.3125rem; background-color: white;\">\n        <p style=\"font-style: italic; color: #555;\">&lt;img&gt;A woman pointing at two sets of apples (red and orange) with the caption “Hmm… Is the income the same?”&lt;/img&gt;</p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <ul style=\"list-style-type: square; margin-left: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.4;\">\n        <li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Income measurement involves judgment.</span></li>\n    </ul>\n    <div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0.625rem 0; border: 0.0625rem dotted #aaa; padding: 0.3125rem; background-color: white;\">\n        <p style=\"font-style: italic; color: #555;\">&lt;img&gt;A flowchart titled “Estimates” listing three factors: • High useful lives • Low warranty costs • Low bad debts. An arrow points to a box labeled “$ High Income,” with the caption “Hey…you might be too optimistic!”&lt;/img&gt;</p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <p style=\"text-align: right; font-size: 0.8em; color: #999; margin-top: 0.9375rem;\">&lt;page_number&gt;Slide 4-5&lt;/page_number&gt;</p>\n    <p style=\"text-align: right; font-size: 1em; font-weight: bold; color: red;\">LO 1</p>\n</div>\n<hr style=\"border: none; border-top: 0.3125rem solid #000;\" />"
      },
      {
        "id": "ch4-p6",
        "type": "equation",
        "html_content": "<div style=\"border: 0.0625rem solid #000; padding: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; background-color: #f0fff0;\">\n    <h2 style=\"text-align: right; color: #333; border-bottom: 0.125rem solid #333; padding-bottom: 0.3125rem;\">Page 6</h2>\n    \n    <header style=\"font-size: 2.5em; font-weight: bold; color: #004d40; border-bottom: 0.1875rem solid #004d40; text-align: center; padding-bottom: 0.625rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;\">INCOME STATEMENT</header>\n    \n    <h2 style=\"color: #006400; margin-bottom: 0.9375rem; border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid #006400;\">Quality of Earnings</h2>\n    \n    <p style=\"font-size: 1.1em;\">Companies have incentives to manage income</p>\n    <ul style=\"list-style-type: circle; margin-left: 1.875rem; line-height: 1.4;\">\n        <li>to meet earnings targets or</li>\n        <li>to make earnings look less risky.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <p style=\"margin-top: 1.25rem;\">\n        <strong style=\"color: darkorange; font-size: 1.2em;\">Earnings management</strong> is the planned timing of revenues, expenses, gains, and losses to smooth out earnings.\n    </p>\n    \n    <p style=\"margin-top: 0.9375rem; border: 0.0625rem solid #aaa; padding: 0.625rem; background-color: white;\">\n        <strong style=\"color: darkred; font-size: 1.2em;\">Quality of earnings</strong> is reduced if earnings management results in information that is less useful for predicting future earnings and cash flows.\n    </p>\n    \n    <p style=\"text-align: right; font-size: 0.8em; color: #999; margin-top: 1.875rem;\">&lt;page_number&gt;Slide 4-6&lt;/page_number&gt;</p>\n    <p style=\"text-align: right; font-size: 1em; font-weight: bold; color: red;\">LO 1</p>\n</div>"
      }
    ]
  }
]
